-- 15-recursive-explanation.cell
-- Explains a concept. Identifies hardest sub-concepts. Explains each.
-- Recurses until all leaf explanations pass a comprehension oracle.
--
-- Tests: вҠўвҠў spawner (recursive tree), вҠўвҲҳ evolution loop,
--        comprehension oracle ("would a 10-year-old understand?"),
--        recursive depth controlled by semantic judgment
--
-- Concept: "How does Cell's confluence property work and why does it matter?"

вҠў concept
  given text вүЎ "How does Cell's confluence property work and why does it matter?"
  yield text

  вҠЁ text names a concept that can be explained at multiple levels of depth

вҠў explain
  given conceptвҶ’text
  yield explanation, jargon-terms[]

  вҲҙ Explain В«conceptвҶ’textВ» clearly and completely. Use plain language where
    possible but don't sacrifice accuracy. After writing the explanation,
    list every technical term or concept you used that a non-expert might
    not understand (the "jargon terms"). These are candidates for recursive
    explanation.

  вҠЁ explanation addresses both "how it works" and "why it matters"
  вҠЁ explanation is 3-8 sentences
  вҠЁ length(jargon-terms) вүҘ 1

вҠў assess-comprehension
  given explainвҶ’explanation
  given explainвҶ’jargon-terms
  yield clear-terms[], hard-terms[], comprehension-score

  вҲҙ For each jargon term in В«explainвҶ’jargon-termsВ», judge:
    Would a curious 10-year-old understand this term from context in the
    explanation В«explainвҶ’explanationВ»?

    Clear: the explanation provides enough context to understand the term
    (e.g., "list" in "a list of items" вҖ” self-evident).
    Hard: the term requires its own explanation (e.g., "topological sort"
    вҖ” not self-evident from context).

    Pick the 3 hardest terms (most opaque, most crucial to understanding).
    Score comprehension 0-10: how well would a 10-year-old understand
    the full explanation?

  вҠЁ length(clear-terms) + length(hard-terms) = length(explainвҶ’jargon-terms)
  вҠЁ length(hard-terms) вүӨ 3
  вҠЁ comprehension-score вҲҲ [0, 10]
  вҠЁ if comprehension-score вүҘ 9 then hard-terms is empty

вҠўвҠў spawn-explainers
  given assess-comprehensionвҶ’hard-terms
  given В§sub-explain-template
  yield В§explainer-cells[]
  until length(explainer-cells) = length(assess-comprehensionвҶ’hard-terms)
  max 5

  вҲҙ For each hard term in В«assess-comprehensionвҶ’hard-termsВ», spawn an
    explainer cell that explains just that term at a 10-year-old's level.

  вҠЁ length(explainer-cells) = length(assess-comprehensionвҶ’hard-terms)

вҠў sub-explain-template
  given term
  given parent-context
  yield explanation, still-hard

  вҲҙ Explain В«termВ» so a curious 10-year-old could understand it.
    Use analogies, examples, and everyday language. The term appeared in
    this context: В«parent-contextВ». Your explanation should make that
    context comprehensible.

    After explaining, judge: does YOUR explanation introduce any term a
    10-year-old wouldn't understand? If yes, mark still-hard = true.

  вҠЁ explanation uses no unexplained jargon
  вҠЁ explanation is 2-5 sentences
  вҠЁ explanation uses at least one analogy or concrete example
  вҠЁ still-hard вҲҲ {true, false}

вҠў collect-explanations
  given explainвҶ’explanation
  given assess-comprehensionвҶ’clear-terms
  given explainer-*вҶ’explanation
  given explainer-*вҶ’still-hard
  yield full-explanation, remaining-hard[], leaf-score

  вҲҙ Assemble a complete explanation by combining:
    1. The main explanation: В«explainвҶ’explanationВ»
    2. Sub-explanations for each hard term from the explainer cells

    Format as a layered explanation: main text first, then "What does X
    mean?" sections for each sub-explained term.

    Check: are any explainer cells still-hard = true? If so, those terms
    need further recursion. Compute leaf-score:
    - 10 if no remaining hard terms
    - Lower proportional to remaining hard terms

  вҠЁ full-explanation includes the main explanation and all sub-explanations
  вҠЁ remaining-hard contains only terms where still-hard = true
  вҠЁ leaf-score = 10 if remaining-hard is empty

вҠў deepen
  given collect-explanationsвҶ’remaining-hard
  given collect-explanationsвҶ’full-explanation
  yield deeper-explanations[]

  вҲҙ For each still-hard term in В«collect-explanationsвҶ’remaining-hardВ»,
    provide a simpler explanation using only words a 10-year-old knows.
    Use analogies from everyday life. No technical terms allowed.

  вҠЁ each deeper explanation uses only everyday language
  вҠЁ each deeper explanation includes an analogy
  вҠЁ length(deeper-explanations) = length(collect-explanationsвҶ’remaining-hard)

вҠўвҲҳ evolve(explain, conceptвҶ’text)
  through collect-explanations, deepen
  until collect-explanationsвҶ’leaf-score вүҘ 9
  max 3

  -- Each iteration: explain the concept вҶ’ assess which terms are hard вҶ’
  -- spawn explainer cells for hard terms вҶ’ collect results вҶ’ if any
  -- sub-explanations still use hard terms, deepen further.
  -- Recursion depth bounded by max 3 and by the comprehension oracle:
  -- the explainer template marks still-hard = false when its explanation
  -- uses only simple terms, terminating that branch.

вҠў format-output
  given collect-explanationsвҶ’full-explanation
  given conceptвҶ’text
  yield final-explanation

  вҲҙ Format В«collect-explanationsвҶ’full-explanationВ» as a clean, readable
    document explaining В«conceptвҶ’textВ». Structure it as:
    1. The main explanation (for someone who knows related concepts)
    2. "Digging deeper" sections for each sub-concept
    3. A one-sentence summary a 10-year-old could repeat

  вҠЁ final-explanation starts with the main explanation
  вҠЁ final-explanation ends with a one-sentence 10-year-old summary
  вҠЁ final-explanation contains no unexplained jargon at any level
